-- Chad Shuts Refinery as CNPC Refuses to Run Plant, Reuters Says
-- B y   R o b e r t   T u t t l e
-- 2012-01-22T07:09:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-22/chad-shuts-refinery-as-cnpc-refuses-to-run-plant-reuters-says.html
Chad  shut its sole refinery after
China National Petroleum Corp., the plant’s majority owner,
refused to produce fuel at the price set by the government,
 Reuters said , citing the country’s Commerce Minister Mahamat
Allahou Taher.  The Chinese director of the refinery will be expelled,
Reuters said. The plant processes 20,000 barrels a day of crude.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Robert Tuttle  in Doha at 
 rtuttle@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
